ormance Engineering and finetuning applications. Experience in latest CI/CD tool chains to ensure zero down time deployments. Secure coding guidelines for OWASP top 10 Vulnerability management. SonarQube Integration for static code analysis. Creation of synthetic tests/monitoring using Datadog. RUM (Real User Monitoring) and Session Replays to track potential issues. Experience in handling Petabytes of data. Strong in Data Structures and Algorithms.","s":"Summary","u":"/cv/","h":"","p":1},{"i":4,"t":"Role​ Created an IoT microservice using Golang http/server modules Microservice has Kafka as a backend Created Kafka consumers to process/write data into timeseries DB Achieved write throughput of 10K msgs/sec to kafka Created middlewares for rate limiting Used uber/zap logger for fast logging Integrated open-telemetry solutions Traces and API metrics were pushed to live reporting system(Jaeger and Grafana) TimeSeries data was aggregated for various intervals To fetch Timeseries data API was created Performance Metrics​ PUT TimeSeries latency within 200 ms for 10K writes/sec GET TimeSeries latency within 800 ms for 2K reads/sec Challenges faced and fixed​ Hot partition in Kafka Poor scaling of consumers Lessons Learnt​ Distribute messages on Kafka using \"Custom keys\" For high rate messages create different topics - avoids noisy neighbours Implement Retry and DLQ topics Achievements​ Service is cloud agnostic Cloud cost was optimized","s":"Golang","u":"/cv/Golang","h":"","p":3}],"index":{"version":"2.3.9","fields":["t"],"fieldVectors":[["t/2",[0,0.727,1,0.727,2,0.191,3,0.727,4,0.727,5,0.727,6,0.727,7,0.727,8,0.727,9,0.191,10,1.25,11,0.259,12,0.727,13,0.727,14,0.727,15,0.259,16,0.727,17,0.727,18,0.727,19,0.984,20,0.259,21,0.191,22,0.191,23,0.984,24,0.727,25,0.315,26,0.727,27,0.191,28,0.727,29,0.984,30,0.984,31,0.727,32,0.727,33,0.191,34,0.727,35,0.727,36,0.727,37,0.727,38,0.727,39,0.727,40,0.727,41,0.727,42,0.727,43,0.727,44,0.727,45,0.984,46,0.727,47,0.727,48,0.727,49,